===message:Hi Keri, I appreciate your opinions and previous statements. However, I think your statement, "We never purposely exterminated any race, never created prison camps where we
KILLED the imprisoned ones, never told Americans that one race was pure, never burned bodies to dispose of, or to rid the evidence of our wrong doings, never made lamp shades out of human skin, we Americans as a whole are NOTHING like the
Nazi population and never will be" is a very strong statement, which I will comment on.  On the surface, it does not seem as if the US never created prison camps where the imprisoned ones were killed.  However, white Americans did not literally say that this was their motive, but essentially this is what they were doing to Native Americans and African-Americans but this is so.  Examples of such is clear throught history, plantations and prisons in the US during the enslavement of African-Americans.  Reservations for Native Americans is a parallel to this as well.  It does not seem as if the US was as delibert as the Nazis but there are similarities which can not be denied, downplayed or discounted.
