===subject:Reply to Keri
===from:Stephenie Buice
===date:Tue Oct 29 20:17:26 2002
===message:I agree that Americans never tried to exterminate another race.  However, I disagree that we are not somewhat like the German Nazi.  Again I will say that Americans never tried to exterminate an entire race, but Americans have views of what the ideal man or woman should look like just like Hitler thought the perfect German was blond hair and blue-eyed.  If you go to the doctor, there are charts that state what weight you should be for your height.  There are more and more plastic surgeons coming into practice everyday.  Why?  Because Americans try to fit the profile of the "perfect" person.  When you fill out an application for a job, some companies ask if you have ever had a mental illness - why?  It shouldn't matter, but it does because it is something that does not fit into the "norm."  I think that while we do not outwardly express our beliefs and opinions, many look at persons with a different appearance and turn their head.
